#### Semantic Data Layer (D024)

```
src/data/
├── glossary.ts         49 terms, 8 categories, SKOS broader/narrower/related, ExternalSource with 4 authority levels (D033)
├── references.ts       28 APA 7th sources, formatAPA() utility
├── observatory.ts      Build-time API fetch, typed interface, fallback snapshot
├── causal-chain.json   CausalChain visualization data
└── ratification-status.json  World map ratification data
```

Glossary and references serve as single source of truth for:
- Human-readable glossary page (`/glossary`)
- Machine-readable JSON-LD endpoints (`/.well-known/`)
- Lens-aware reference lists on ArticleLayout
- BaseLayout structured data (@graph with BreadcrumbList, DefinedTermSet)

#### Cross-Linking Strategy

Topology: **mesh** (D024 transformed the original hub-and-spoke into cross-linked mesh)

Every ICESCR article page links to:
- The relevant AI analysis section showing how that right gets affected
- The relevant evidence/data supporting the connection
- The relevant action items (what to say to senators about THIS right)
- Related ICESCR articles addressing connected rights
- Glossary terms for project-specific vocabulary

Every analysis page links to:
- The ICESCR article(s) it connects to
- The underlying evidence
- The methodology explanation
- Glossary definitions for first-use abbreviations

Section indexes include cross-section navigation callouts:
- Covenant → "See how AI affects these rights" → Connection
- Gap → "What ratification would change" → Connection/Counterfactual
- Evidence → "These numbers connect to your rights" → Covenant

This creates a web of reinforcing content rather than a linear reading path.

#### Visualization Architecture

```
COMPONENT (FILE)           │ TYPE         │ PAGES                        │ DATA SOURCE          │ STATUS
───────────────────────────┼──────────────┼──────────────────────────────┼──────────────────────┼────────
RatificationMap.svelte     │ D3-geo map   │ /                            │ ratification-status  │ ✓ D013
Timeline.svelte            │ CSS+Svelte   │ /gap/timeline                │ Hardcoded events     │ ✓ D013
CausalChain.svelte         │ SVG+Svelte   │ /connection (2 pages)        │ causal-chain.json    │ ✓ D019
Quiz.svelte                │ CSS+Svelte   │ /covenant/quiz               │ Hardcoded questions  │ ✓
ScoreChart.svelte          │ Pure SVG     │ /connection (2) /evidence (1)│ Inline Astro props   │ ✓ D020
RadarChart.svelte          │ Pure SVG     │ /connection/dignity-quotient │ Inline Astro props   │ ✓ D020
Sankey (V7)                │ —            │ —                            │ No flow data exists  │ Deferred
```

#### Accessibility Architecture

- WCAG 2.1 AA minimum, AAA target for text content
- All visualizations have text alternatives
- All interactive elements keyboard-navigable
- Reading level: 8th grade for summaries, college level for analysis
- Progressive enhancement: core content works without JavaScript
- Screen reader testing with NVDA and VoiceOver

---

## Technology Stack (DECIDED — D012)

**Astro + MDX + Svelte Islands + D3/Layercake**

Selected via full differential diagnosis through Orders 0–4. See plan.md.decisions D012.

```
LAYER              │ TECHNOLOGY          │ PURPOSE
───────────────────┼─────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────
Static generation  │ Astro 4+            │ Content-first SSG; zero JS default
Content authoring  │ MDX                 │ Markdown + component embedding
Interactive islands│ Svelte 5            │ Compiled components, no runtime
Visualizations     │ D3.js + Layercake   │ Full viz power + Svelte-native charts
Styling            │ TBD (CSS/Tailwind)  │ CSS-driven lens layout transformation
Deployment         │ Cloudflare Pages    │ CDN-level domain routing; edge functions
                   │ or Vercel/Netlify   │ if needed for senator lookup API
```

### Content Pipeline

```
content/*.mdx
  → Astro content collections (typed frontmatter)
    → lens-aware Astro layouts
      → static HTML + Svelte islands (client:visible)
        → CDN deployment
```

### Lens System Architecture

```
BaseLayout.astro
  ├── <LensProvider client:load>        Svelte island
  │   ├── reads: URL param ?lens=       highest priority
  │   ├── reads: sessionStorage         per-page override
  │   ├── reads: localStorage           session default
  │   ├── reads: route path             entry-point detection
  │   ├── fallback: voter               advocacy-first default (D017)
  │   └── sets: data-lens on <body>
  │
  ├── <body data-lens="voter|politician|developer|educator|researcher">
  │   │
  │   ├── CSS layout rules (5 lenses):
  │   │   [data-lens="voter"]      → personal impact, action-oriented (default)
  │   │   [data-lens="politician"] → policy framing, legislative pathways
  │   │   [data-lens="developer"]  → dense, data-forward, monospace tables
  │   │   [data-lens="educator"]   → learning-objective framing, downloads prominent
  │   │   [data-lens="researcher"] → structured abstracts, citations, BibTeX
  │   │
  │   ├── Lens-specific content sections (ArticleLayout, D019):
  │   │   voter:      .personal-impact  → "What This Means for You" + action CTA
  │   │   politician: .policy-summary   → Policy brief (right, status, AI, committee)
  │   │   educator:   .learning-objectives + .discussion-prompt
  │   │   researcher: .structured-abstract
  │   │
  │   ├── Section reordering via CSS order property
  │   ├── Conditional visibility via display: none/block
  │   └── View Transitions API for smooth switch animation
  │
  └── Interactive islands (Svelte, client:visible)
      ├── Receive lens as prop from LensProvider store
      └── CausalChain: 5 render paths per lens (D019)
          ├── educator   → accordion (pedagogical, order-by-order)
          ├── developer  → SVG flowchart (technical, interactive graph)
          ├── voter      → impact narrative (personal cards, action CTA)
          ├── politician → executive brief (one-screen policy summary)
          └── researcher → step-through (analytical, confidence levels)
```

### Theme System Architecture (D018)

```
<html data-theme="dark">                ← Set on <html>, not <body>
  <head>
    <script>                            ← Blocking (inline, runs before paint)
      reads: localStorage('unratified-theme')
      reads: prefers-color-scheme media query
      fallback: light (no attribute = light default)
      if dark: sets data-theme="dark" on <html>
    </script>
    <meta name="theme-color" content>   ← Updated by script + ThemeToggle
  </head>
  <body data-lens="voter">             ← Lens on body, theme on html (clean separation)
    <nav>
      <LensToggle client:load />
      <ThemeToggle client:load />       ← Two-button radiogroup: Light | Dark
    </nav>
  </body>
</html>

CSS cascade:
  :root {                              ← Light palette (default, no JS required)
    --color-bg: #fafafa;
    --color-text: #37474f;
    --color-heading: #33691e;
    --color-accent: #00695c;
    --color-map-ratified: #2e7d32;
    --color-node-root: #263238;
    /* ... */
  }
  [data-theme="dark"] {                ← Dark terminal palette override
    --color-bg: #002d38;
    --color-text: #98a8a8;
    --color-heading: #819500;
    --color-accent: #259d94;
    --color-map-ratified: #4a7c59;
    --color-node-root: #8faaab;
    /* ... */
  }
```

Theme resolution priority: URL `?theme=` > localStorage > `prefers-color-scheme` > light

### Deployment Architecture

NOTE: observatory.unratified.org lives in a separate project/agent,
preparing for a soft launch targeting Hacker News (news.ycombinator.com).
This project handles unratified.org only. Cross-linking uses standard hyperlinks.

```
Astro project (unratified.org)
  src/pages/
    index.astro                    → unratified.org/
    covenant/index.astro           → unratified.org/covenant/
    covenant/articles/[id].astro   → unratified.org/covenant/articles/6
    gap/index.astro                → unratified.org/gap/
    educators/index.astro          → unratified.org/educators/
    action/index.astro             → unratified.org/action/
    resources/index.astro          → unratified.org/resources/
```

